At the last minute, when I had to put together a custom catered menu for an event, this restaurant was the only one who made it happen with no fuss. I remembered this restaurant from ordering-in, and figured I’d try them. Edwin was super helpful and patient in listening to my requests, and seeing how they could reasonably rise to the occasion. In the end, the meal was well prepared, packaged, and delicious. People are still talking about the food!  In short,… they listen, they plan, their prices are reasonable, the food is delicious and there was no fuss.  I HIGHLY recommend considering this restaurant for dining or your next event.

DOMINICAN REPUBLIC 🇩🇴 Eat the World NYC review: The singing didn't stop from the moment I entered until presumably long after I left. The staff here continued to work as they were caught in some stage between lip syncing and full-on belting out the pop and reggaeton videos playing on the TV. Behind the steam table at the entry, showcasing the specials of the day, this friendly crew was all smiles and efficiency at the same time.  I opted for a few Presidentes and an order of the mofongo smothered in char-grilled beef. This gigantic plate only ran $10, beers $3. Really had me wishing I could spend the rest of the evening here.

If you like Spanish food, then this is already the go to place. I've eaten at this place for a long time and their food is delicious, and they never disappoint on the quality. But like every restaurant, they have it's problems. For one, the staff usually only speaks Spanish, and has a hard time understanding English speakers. Second, the staff can also be quite rude and may even give you off to another waiter or server to deal with you - even if you're a Spanish speaker. Last of all, they put too much vinegar in their salad, so unless you like lots of vinegar in your salad, either don't get it or simply don't ask for vinegar.  If you're in the neighborhood and in the mood for Spanish food, go here. If you're close by but don't feel like walking, order through Seamless. I recommend ordering from here than Nancy's which is right across the street.
